{"id":"diceforge-swade-core","name":"SWADE Core Rules Reference Builds","version":"1.1","author":"DiceForge Studios","description":"All 47 vehicles from Savage Worlds core rulebook (pp.82-86). Weapon loadouts verified line-by-line against canon.","vehicles":[{"name":"Bicycle","size":-1,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Two wheels, no motor, no armour, no dignity. Half of all shots hit the rider instead.","notes":"The bicycle is invisible. Nobody notices one more cyclist on a city street, which makes it the perfect surveillance and courier vehicle for low-tech campaigns. In chase scenes, she squeezes through gaps no car can follow \u2014 alleys, stairwells, crowded markets. 50% of shots hit the rider rather than the vehicle.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":-3,"handlingLevel":0,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":16},{"name":"Horse-Drawn Carriage","size":3,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four wheels, one horse, variable passenger comfort. Stagecoaches, hansoms, and broughams all fall here.","notes":"The carriage is your chase vehicle for historical and fantasy campaigns. Stagecoach robberies, runaway horses, rooftop leaps onto the luggage rack \u2014 she exists to create cinematic moments. Horse-drawn, so she stops when the horses do.","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":-3,"handlingLevel":-3,"woundsLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top","towing"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":16},{"name":"Early Automobile","size":3,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Crank-start, top-heavy, and terrifying at speed. Model Ts, Tin Lizzies, and their ilk.","notes":"The Model T generation. Slow, temperamental, and revolutionary. She puts your campaign on wheels for the first time \u2014 Prohibition rum-runners, early pulp adventures, the first getaway cars. Temperamental enough to create complications at the worst possible moment.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":-2,"handlingLevel":-2,"woundsLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","temperamental"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":40},{"name":"Street Motorcycle","size":1,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Stock road bike \u2014 Harleys, Ducatis, or the local equivalent. Fast, exposed, and half the shots hit the rider.","notes":"The street bike is your urban pursuit vehicle. She splits lanes, she threads traffic, she fits where cars can\\'t follow. The rider is exposed \u2014 50% of shots hit them rather than the bike. That vulnerability is the price of agility.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"woundsLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":1,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Off-Road Motorcycle","size":0,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Knobby tyres, excellent suspension, questionable life choices. Trail bikes, enduros, and motocross machines.","notes":"The dirt bike goes where roads don\\'t. She\\'s the jungle recon vehicle, the desert patrol bike, the mountain courier. Four-wheel drive equivalent for two wheels \u2014 she ignores terrain that stops wheeled vehicles cold.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top","all_terrain","four_wd"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":80},{"name":"Compact Car","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Economy hatchback. Honda Civics, Ford Fiestas, and a thousand forgettable commuter boxes.","notes":"The compact car is your default civilian vehicle. Every NPC drives one, every parking lot is full of them, every car chase starts or ends with one. Mechanically unremarkable, which is exactly the point \u2014 she\\'s the baseline everything else is measured against.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":1,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Mid-Size Sedan","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four doors, air bags, reasonable legroom. Your Camrys, Accords, and fleet rental staples.","notes":"The family sedan. She carries more passengers and gear than the compact, handles roughly the same, and blends into traffic just as easily. The car your players borrow, steal, or commandeer when they need to move without attracting attention.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","cargo_bay"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":4,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Family Minivan","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Sliding doors, cup holders, existential surrender. The vehicle of parenthood.","notes":"The minivan carries a full party plus gear. She\\'s the team vehicle for modern campaigns \u2014 the thing everyone piles into when the job starts. Not fast, not tough, but she holds everyone and their equipment in one vehicle.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","cargo_bay"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":7,"mphOverride":90},{"name":"Sport Utility Vehicle","size":5,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four-wheel drive, luxury features, poor fuel economy. Range Rovers to Cherokees.","notes":"The SUV bridges civilian comfort and rough terrain capability. Four-wheel drive gets her off-road where sedans can\\'t follow. She\\'s the vehicle of choice for private security, rural law enforcement, and players who expect trouble outside city limits.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","four_wd","all_terrain"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":7,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Sports Car","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Two doors, low profile, speed over practicality. Mustangs, Camaros, and mid-life crises.","notes":"The sports car wins chases through speed and handling. She\\'s fast on straights, nimble in corners, and utterly useless off-road or in bad weather. The vehicle your players lust after and the one that gets them into trouble.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":3,"handlingLevel":2,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":160},{"name":"Semi-Truck","size":9,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Cab and trailer. Peterbilts, Kenworths, Scanias \u2014 the kings of the motorway.","notes":"The semi-truck is your convoy centrepiece and your roadblock. She can\\'t manoeuvre, she can\\'t hide, and she takes a long time to stop. But she carries anything, tows anything, and at highway speed she\\'s an unstoppable battering ram. Trailer: Size 7, Toughness 14(2).","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","cargo_bay","towing","loud"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-4,"passengers":1,"mphOverride":75},{"name":"WW2 Light Utility Vehicle","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four-wheel drive workhorse. The Willys Jeep, Kubelwagen, and GAZ-67 kept armies moving.","notes":"The jeep goes everywhere and carries everything. She\\'s the workhorse of military campaigns from WWII to Vietnam \u2014 reconnaissance, command vehicle, ambulance, weapons platform. Open-topped and lightly armoured, which means the crew is always one burst away from disaster. Four-wheel drive.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"pintle","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","open_top","four_wd"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":1,"passengers":3,"mphOverride":65},{"name":"WW2 Medium Tank","size":8,"loco":"tracked","desc":"The workhorse Allied tank. Shermans, Cromwells, and their equivalents \u2014 reliable, mass-produced, outgunned by late-war heavies.","notes":"The workhorse of the Allied armoured forces. She wasn\\'t the best tank of the war \u2014 the Germans outgunned her routinely \u2014 but there were always more Shermans. Use her as the reliable, available option that wins through numbers and logistics rather than individual superiority. Heavy Armor, Tracked.","armourLevel":1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_75mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"pintle","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":30},{"name":"WW2 Medium Tank (Soviet)","size":7,"loco":"tracked","desc":"Sloped front armour, rugged and simple. The T-34 and its derivatives defined the Eastern Front.","notes":"The T-34 changed tank warfare. Her sloped armour deflected shots that would penetrate a flat-faced Sherman, and she was simple enough to build in staggering numbers. The backbone of the Soviet armoured force and the benchmark for medium tank design. Heavy Armor, Sloped Armor (front), Tracked.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":2,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_76mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"turret","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":3,"mphOverride":35},{"name":"WW2 Medium Tank (Axis)","size":7,"loco":"tracked","desc":"The backbone of Axis armoured divisions. Panzer IVs, StuGs, and their upgunned variants.","notes":"The Panzer IV was Germany\\'s reliable medium tank \u2014 not as famous as the Tiger, not as advanced as the Panther, but available in numbers and effective across the entire war. She\\'s the opponent your players face most often in a European theatre campaign. Heavy Armor, Tracked.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":3,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_75mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"turret","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":4,"mphOverride":25},{"name":"WW2 Heavy Tank","size":8,"loco":"tracked","desc":"Massive, over-engineered, and terrifying. Tigers, IS-2s, and Pershings \u2014 the heavyweights that broke through and broke down.","notes":"The King Tiger is your named threat. She outguns everything the Allies field and her frontal armour shrugs off most anti-tank weapons. Use her as a boss encounter \u2014 the players hear her coming, they plan around her, and they need a clever approach because a straight fight is suicide. Heavy Armor, Tracked.","toughLevel":2,"armourLevel":3,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_88mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"turret","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","famous"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":25},{"name":"Cold War Main Battle Tank","size":9,"loco":"tracked","desc":"Exported to half the world. T-72s, T-62s, and Chieftains \u2014 rugged, adequate, everywhere.","notes":"The T-72 is the world\\'s most exported tank. She shows up everywhere \u2014 every regional conflict, every arms deal, every third-world army. Not as capable as Western designs but available, affordable, and dangerous enough. Heavy Armor, Tracked.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":6,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_125mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg_modern","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg_modern","mount":"pintle","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-2,"mphOverride":50},{"name":"Modern Main Battle Tank (Eastern)","size":8,"loco":"tracked","desc":"Advanced fire control, composite armour, improved stabiliser. T-80s, T-90s, and Merkava IVs.","notes":"The T-80 is the Soviet answer to the Abrams \u2014 faster, lower-profile, and equipped with reactive armour. She represents the top tier of opposition for Cold War and modern campaigns. Heavy Armor, Night Vision, Tracked.","toughLevel":2,"armourLevel":9,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_125mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg_modern","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg_modern","mount":"pintle","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-2,"mphOverride":43},{"name":"Cold War Wheeled APC","size":6,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Eight wheels, amphibious, cramped. BTR-series, Strykers, and Piranhas \u2014 gets troops there alive, mostly.","notes":"The BTR-70 carries infantry into combat and provides fire support with her turret-mounted weapons. She swims rivers without preparation, which changes the tactical map \u2014 obstacles that stop wheeled vehicles don\\'t stop a BTR. Amphibious, 4WD, Heavy Armor.","toughLevel":2,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"hmg_modern","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg_modern","mount":"turret","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","amphibious","four_wd"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":1,"passengers":8,"mphOverride":49},{"name":"Hover Tank","size":7,"loco":"hover","desc":"Grav-drive heavy armour with energy weapons. No terrain penalties, no mercy.","notes":"The hover tank represents the next generation of armoured warfare. She ignores terrain, crosses water without slowing, and positions faster than any tracked vehicle. The trade-off is that hover vehicles can\\'t dig in \u2014 she fights on the move or not at all. Heavy Armor, Hover, Night Vision.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":9,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"laser_heavy","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"laser_gat","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":3,"mphOverride":45},{"name":"Hover APC","size":7,"loco":"hover","desc":"Grav-drive troop transport. Fast, sealed, carries a platoon over any surface.","notes":"The hover APC delivers troops across any terrain at speed. She\\'s the future of mechanised infantry \u2014 rivers, rubble, swamp, and rough ground are no longer obstacles. Heavy Armor, Hover.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":3,"speedLevel":2,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"laser_gat","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":1,"passengers":14,"mphOverride":75},{"name":"Civilian Biplane","size":4,"loco":"turboprop","desc":"Open cockpit, fabric wings, a romantic way to die. Barnstormers, crop dusters, and Tiger Moths.","notes":"The biplane is your inter-war and pulp adventure aircraft. She\\'s slow enough that the players can shoot pistols from the cockpit, low enough to barnstorm, and fragile enough that every bullet matters. Open cockpit, wind in your face, goggles and scarves.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":-2,"handlingLevel":1,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top","short_range"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":125},{"name":"Light Civilian Aircraft","size":5,"loco":"turboprop","desc":"Single-engine four-seater. Cessnas, Pipers, and Beechcrafts \u2014 the most common aircraft in the sky.","notes":"The Cessna is your civilian light aircraft. She\\'s the plane the players charter, steal, or escape in. Simple to fly, cheap to hire, and she lands on dirt strips that would destroy anything bigger. The most produced aircraft in history for a reason.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-2,"handlingLevel":1,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":140},{"name":"Civilian Helicopter","size":7,"loco":"vtol","desc":"General-purpose rotorcraft. Bell 206s, Robinson R44s \u2014 news, medevac, tourism, escape.","notes":"The civilian helicopter\\'s unique ability is hover and vertical landing. She doesn\\'t need a runway. Use her for medical evacuation, news coverage, executive transport, and dramatic rooftop extractions. VTOL.","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":0,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","stol"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":130},{"name":"Executive Jet","size":8,"loco":"jet","desc":"Fast, comfortable, and proof that someone is doing well. Learjets, Gulfstreams, Citations.","notes":"The Learjet is your fast long-range transport. She gets the players across continents in hours, and her presence tells them something about whoever owns it \u2014 money, connections, urgency. She\\'s also a beautiful target sitting on a runway.","armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":3,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","spacious","long_range"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-3,"passengers":10,"mphOverride":540},{"name":"Space Shuttle","size":13,"loco":"jet","desc":"Reusable orbital vehicle. Three main engines, two solid boosters, one fragile heat shield.","notes":"The shuttle is your near-future and hard sci-fi reference point. She demonstrates that size and Toughness don\\'t always correlate with combat power \u2014 the shuttle is large but fragile, designed for a specific mission rather than a fight.","armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":5,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","sealed","pressurised"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-19,"passengers":40,"mphOverride":17000},{"name":"WW2 Heavy Bomber","size":10,"loco":"turboprop","desc":"Four engines, ten crew, bristling with defensive guns. B-17s, Lancasters, and He-111s \u2014 strategic bombing incarnate.","notes":"The Flying Fortress is your strategic bomber and your crew survival scenario. She carries ten men, she bristles with defensive guns, and she has to hold formation through flak and fighters for hours. Every mission is a survival horror session at 25,000 feet.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-4,"handlingLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"turret","linked":1},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"turret","linked":1},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"bombs_ww","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","long_range"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":5,"mphOverride":115},{"name":"WW2 Fighter (Axis)","size":6,"loco":"turboprop","desc":"Single-seat, single-engine interceptor. Bf-109s, Fw-190s, and Macchis dominated early-war skies.","notes":"The Messerschmitt is Germany\\'s primary fighter across the entire war. She\\'s fast, she climbs well, and her cannon armament hits hard. The opposition your players face in every European air combat scenario from the Battle of Britain to Berlin.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"cannon_20mm","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1}],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":380},{"name":"WW2 Fighter (Allied, Late-War)","size":7,"loco":"turboprop","desc":"Long-range escort fighter. Mustangs, Thunderbolts, and Tempests \u2014 six-plus guns and the legs to use them.","notes":"The Mustang is the best all-round fighter of the war. She escorts bombers to Berlin and back, she dogfights anything the Luftwaffe sends up, and she strafes ground targets on the way home. The player character\\'s fighter of choice.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1}],"specials":["enclosed","long_range"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":437},{"name":"WW2 Fighter (Pacific)","size":6,"loco":"turboprop","desc":"Exceptional range and manoeuvrability, paid for with zero armour protection. Zeros, Oscars, and their kin.","notes":"The Zero trades armour for agility. She turns inside anything the Allies fly, which makes her lethal in a dogfight \u2014 until the first bullet hits, because she has no armour and no self-sealing fuel tanks. Glass cannon in aircraft form.","armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1},{"weaponId":"cannon_20mm","mount":"fixed","linked":1}],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":350},{"name":"WW2 Fighter (Allied, Early-War)","size":6,"loco":"turboprop","desc":"Eight machine guns, elliptical wings, and the Battle of Britain. Spitfires, Hurricanes, and P-40s.","notes":"The Spitfire is Britain\\'s finest. She matches the Bf-109 in speed, outturns it at most altitudes, and her elliptical wing is the most recognisable silhouette of the war. The Battle of Britain in one aircraft.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":1}],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":360},{"name":"Modern Attack Helicopter","size":8,"loco":"vtol","desc":"Tandem cockpit, chain gun, guided missiles. Apaches, Hinds, and Tigers \u2014 the apex predators.","notes":"The Apache is your modern attack helicopter \u2014 she finds targets with her sensor suite, kills them with Hellfire missiles, and moves on before anyone can shoot back. Use her to demonstrate the terrifying gap between infantry and modern air power. Helicopter, Night Vision.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"autocannon_30mm","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hellfire","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-3,"mphOverride":225},{"name":"VTOL Strike Fighter","size":7,"loco":"vtol","desc":"Vertical takeoff, subsonic, ground attack specialist. Harriers, Yak-38s, and their successors.","notes":"The Harrier operates from roads, clearings, and ships too small for conventional aircraft. Her VTOL capability means she can be anywhere the enemy doesn\\'t expect close air support. Slow for a jet, devastating for anything on the ground. VTOL.","speedLevel":3,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"autocannon_25mm","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"sidewinder","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"bombs_mod","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["enclosed","stol"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":630},{"name":"Modern Air Superiority Fighter","size":9,"loco":"jet","desc":"Twin-engine, Mach 2.5, designed to own the sky. Eagles, Flankers, Typhoons, and Rafales.","notes":"The Eagle has never been shot down in air-to-air combat. She\\'s the benchmark for air superiority fighters \u2014 fast, well-armed, and equipped with sensors that let her fight beyond visual range. The thing your players hear about but never want to see. Night Vision.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":3,"handlingLevel":3,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"cannon_20mm","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"sidewinder","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"sparrow","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-4,"mphOverride":1875},{"name":"Modern Multirole Fighter (Eastern)","size":9,"loco":"jet","desc":"Long-range interceptor. Flankers, Fulcrums, and their export derivatives.","notes":"The Flanker is the Soviet answer to the F-15 \u2014 arguably more manoeuvrable, certainly more dramatic in appearance, and equipped to fight at every range. She represents peer-level opposition for any modern air combat campaign. Night Vision.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":2,"handlingLevel":2,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"autocannon_30mm","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"sidewinder","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"sparrow","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-4,"mphOverride":1550},{"name":"Vietnam-Era Utility Helicopter","size":7,"loco":"vtol","desc":"The sound of the rotors IS the war. Hueys, Pumas, and Mi-8s \u2014 the workhorse of every conflict since.","notes":"The Huey is the sound of the Vietnam War. Her distinctive rotor beat tells everyone \u2014 friendly and hostile \u2014 that she\\'s coming. She carries troops, she evacuates wounded, she provides fire support, and she defines the helicopter warfare era. Helicopter.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":2,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":3,"passengers":12,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Age of Sail Warship","size":14,"loco":"water_sail","desc":"Three masts, multiple gun decks, the capital ship of the age of sail. Galleons, men-o-war, and ships of the line.","notes":"The galleon is your Age of Sail warship and your pirate campaign flagship. She carries dozens of guns, a crew of hundreds, and enough provisions for months at sea. She\\'s a floating fortress, a mobile settlement, and a slow-moving target for anything faster. Heavy Armor.","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"med_cannon_bp","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"med_cannon_bp","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"med_cannon_bp","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"med_cannon_bp","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":80,"mphOverride":9},{"name":"Ancient War Galley","size":13,"loco":"water_sail","desc":"Oars and sails. Triremes, biremes, and dromons \u2014 ram the enemy, board the wreckage.","notes":"The galley is your ancient and medieval warship. Oars give her independence from wind \u2014 she moves when and where the captain commands, which makes her the dominant naval platform from Greece to Lepanto. Her ram is as dangerous as her weapons. Heavy Armor, Oars+Sails.","armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"ballista","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","ram_plate"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":100,"mphOverride":20},{"name":"Hydrofoil","size":10,"loco":"water_turbo","desc":"Foil-borne at speed, hull-borne at rest. Fast and smooth in calm water, miserable in rough.","notes":"The hydrofoil lifts out of the water at speed, reducing drag and dramatically increasing velocity. She\\'s your fast patrol and intercept vessel for coastal operations \u2014 faster than conventional boats, more agile, and harder to hit at speed.","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":2,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-4,"passengers":9,"mphOverride":70},{"name":"River Patrol Boat","size":7,"loco":"water_turbo","desc":"Shallow draft, heavy weapons, brown-water navy. PBRs, Swift Boats, and their equivalents.","notes":"The PBR is your brown-water navy vessel \u2014 rivers, estuaries, coastlines. She\\'s small enough to navigate shallow waterways that would ground larger craft, and armed enough to suppress fire from both banks. The Vietnam riverine warfare workhorse. Heavy Armor.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"pintle","linked":1},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":3,"mphOverride":32},{"name":"WW2 Torpedo Boat","size":12,"loco":"water_turbo","desc":"Fast, wooden, expendable. PT boats, E-boats, and MTBs \u2014 torpedo runs under fire.","notes":"The PT boat is your fast attack craft \u2014 she closes with the enemy at speed, launches torpedoes, and gets out before the return fire finds her. Small crew, high risk, enormous potential reward if the torpedoes hit. JFK commanded one. thick plating.","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":3,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"pintle","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"pintle","linked":0},{"weaponId":"torpedo_ww","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"torpedo_ww","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"torpedo_ww","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"torpedo_ww","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-10,"mphOverride":40},{"name":"Rowboat","size":0,"loco":"water_turbo","desc":"Two oars, no motor, unlimited splinters. Dinghies, skiffs, and anything you can row.","notes":"The rowboat is your insertion vehicle. She\\'s silent, she\\'s invisible against a dark shoreline, and she carries a small team to wherever they need to be without alerting anyone. Also the thing that\\'s between your players and drowning when the ship sinks.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-3,"handlingLevel":-3,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top","shallow_draft"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":5},{"name":"Speed Boat","size":4,"loco":"water_turbo","desc":"Outboard motor, fibreglass hull, weekend fun. Ski boats, bass boats, and cigarette racers.","notes":"The speedboat is your modern chase vehicle on water. Fast, agile, and fragile \u2014 she\\'s the equivalent of a sports car on the open sea. Drug runners, coast guard, and players who need to be somewhere coastal in a hurry.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":2,"handlingLevel":1,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":90},{"name":"Small Yacht","size":8,"loco":"water_turbo","desc":"Comfortable coastal cruiser. Forty feet of fibreglass, teak, and someone else paying the marina fees.","notes":"The yacht is a location, not a chase vehicle. She\\'s where the party happens, where the deal goes down, where the villain entertains guests while the players infiltrate from the waterline. Comfortable, expensive, and conspicuous.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","spacious","long_range"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-4,"passengers":9,"mphOverride":35},{"name":"WW2 Light Tank","size":7,"loco":"tracked","desc":"Fast reconnaissance armour. Stuarts, Luchs, and T-70s \u2014 light gun, light armour, big heart.","notes":"The Stuart is your light tank \u2014 fast, undergunned, and used for reconnaissance rather than direct engagement. She scouts ahead of the main force, finds the enemy, and calls in the Shermans. Players driving Stuarts should feel the tension of bringing a light tank to a heavy fight. Heavy Armor, Tracked.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":2,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_37mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"pintle","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":3,"mphOverride":36},{"name":"Modern Main Battle Tank","size":9,"loco":"tracked","desc":"Composite armour, thermal sights, stabilised gun. Abrams, Challenger 2, Leopard 2 \u2014 the Western benchmark.","notes":"The modern benchmark for main battle tanks. Her combination of composite armour, stabilised gun, and thermal imaging makes her dominant in open terrain. Use her to show players what modern military hardware can do \u2014 and to remind them that even the best tank is vulnerable in cities. Heavy Armor, Night Vision, Tracked.","toughLevel":2,"armourLevel":10,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_120mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg_modern","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg_modern","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg_modern","mount":"pintle","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-1,"mphOverride":40},{"name":"Modern Infantry Fighting Vehicle","size":7,"loco":"tracked","desc":"Autocannon, anti-tank missiles, carries a full squad. Bradleys, Warriors, and BMPs.","notes":"The Bradley is an infantry fighting vehicle \u2014 she carries troops and fights alongside them. Her autocannon shreds light vehicles and her TOW missiles threaten tanks. The players either ride in her or face her, and both experiences should feel dangerous. Heavy Armor, Night Vision, Tracked.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":1,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"autocannon_25mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg_modern","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"tow_missile","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":2,"passengers":7,"mphOverride":40}]}